				<li id="16745585" class="cmnt-root" data="26" data-d="1658982644000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579521/Blasphemous-Claw" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">28 Jul 2022 00:30</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16745585" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">The moment I parried the Black Blade might be one of the most satisfying moments in this game. Maliketh is an insanely hard, high-pressure boss that is constantly either moving acrobatically out of melee range or chasing you down, and the combination of his sheer damage per hit and Destined Death effects means that you&apos;re punished severely for every single hit, including trades. Doing this fight &quot;fairly&quot; if you&apos;re mostly a melee character is an agonizing exercise in scrapping for every safe hit. But you&apos;re not SUPPOSED to play it this way. I think that the Blasphemous Claw was added not just as a reward for explorative players, but as a key aspect of this fight as an experience, to where if you&apos;re playing without it, the game is either punishing your incuriosity with added difficulty or is aware that you&apos;re self-handicapping yourself. The Blasphemous Claw levels the playing field between you and Maliketh&apos;s extraordinarily punishing Destined Death attack; it&apos;s no coincidence that the one attack that you can parry is the single most visually spectacular in an already spectacular fight.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16745585" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16745585" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>29</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16745585"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16745585" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16745585"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
